node.text:
So y’all know that I hardly ever do ads, but when I find a healing product that I 100% truly believe in, (and has helped with my own healing journey) I NEED to tell you about it! 
〰️
@healthpersonas is a new healthcare company that provides accessible health coaching through video chat with your own personal healer. 
〰️
They have this awesome assessment called the KNOW ME assessment, which helps you to gain valuable insights into your true self including your strengths and areas of improvement.
〰️
Then they connect you with a  health expert that provides you with a deeper understanding of your results!
〰️
My HealthGuide was so knowledgable and she helped me learn so much more about what areas of my life that I’m most motivated by, which is my need for security and meaningful relationships (SO TRUE)!
〰️
It was so cool to see a more in-depth look into what may be lacking in my life and how to focus more on attaining more fulfillment.
〰️
Check out the link in my bio to download the app👉 @theanxietyhealer ....click on 'social media referral' upon checkout, and take the KNOW ME assessment to see what type of results turn up for you! myhealthpersona.com/app
〰️
If you are interested in full access of the app, you can always click on ‘social media referral’ upon checkout and get your first 30 days for only $4.99! Happy healing y’all!
〰️
#HealthPersonas #knowmetest #anxietyrecovery #mentalhealthrecovery #mentalhealthresource #anxietyawareness #anxietyfighter #anxietyhelp #theanxietyhealer #ad

Photo shared by The Anxiety Healer on September 01, 2021 tagging @theanxietyhealer, and @theanxietychicks. May be an image of text that says 'Acknowledge what you are feeling and name all of the choices you made that day @theanxietyhealer "I chose to get dressed" or "I chose to get in my car" *choices help remind us that we are more in control than we might think'.

Photo shared by The Anxiety Healer on September 01, 2021 tagging @theanxietyhealer, and @theanxietychicks. May be an image of text that says 'Breathe in for 4 seconds Hold for 4 seconds @theanxietyhealer Breath out for 6 seconds *until you feel yourself de-escalate'.

Photo shared by The Anxiety Healer on September 01, 2021 tagging @theanxietyhealer, and @theanxietychicks. May be an image of text that says 'Bring ice water with @theanxietyheale you *take small sips when feeling anxious or splash some on your face. The cold temperature has been shown to help decrease cortisol (a stress-inducing hormone).'.

Photo shared by The Anxiety Healer on September 01, 2021 tagging @theanxietyhealer, and @theanxietychicks. May be an image of text that says 'boo Blast the air conditioner @theanxietyhealer *for the same reason as why you should bring ice water'.

Photo shared by The Anxiety Healer on September 01, 2021 tagging @theanxietyhealer, and @theanxietychicks. May be an image of text that says 'Use your 5 senses to bring your mind back into the present moment. @theanxietyhealer *say aloud 3 things you can see, hear, smell, touch, & taste'.

node.text:
You can’t always physically be with someone you love when they have a panic attack, but here are some tips on how you can help over the phone!
〰️
The one that helps me the most is the reminder that it will pass and that the panic is only temporary!
〰️
What is the best way someone can help you over the phone if you’re having a panic attack? Let me know in the comments ⬇️⬇️⬇️
〰️
Follow 👉 @theanxietyhealer for all things anxiety healing!
〰️
Post by @myanxiety_and_me

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by The Anxiety Healer on August 31, 2021 tagging @theanxietyhealer, and @myanxiety_and_me. May be an image of text that says 'How to help 100 someone having a panic attack over the phone @MyAnxiety_and_Me'.

Photo by The Anxiety Healer on August 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Accept the silence. Sometimes just being on the phone with them helps Tell them to move toasafe, a safe, quiet place they to are comfortable with Reassure them you there you re not leaving @MyAnxiety_and_Me'.

Photo by The Anxiety Healer on August 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'They are vulnerable, make them feel loved and cared about Remind them that the panic attack will eventually pass Reassure them that the panic attack cannot hurt them @MyAnxiety_and_Me'.

Photo by The Anxiety Healer on August 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'When the attack has passed give them time space to calm down Tell them to take deep breaths breathe slowly with them Speak to them in simple sentences with a slow, calm voice @MyAnxiety_and_Me'.

Photo by The Anxiety Healer on August 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'The best thing we can do for someone who is having a panic attack is be there for them, not judge them and show empathy. Ifa friend, family member, or anyone asks you for help during a panic attack, knon that they trust you and feel like they can be vulnerable around you. Iyou don 't know what to do, just be there for them till the end. @MyAnxiety_and_Me'.

node.text:
How I kicked anxiety in the a** last weekend! Felt like I was at a level 9 as I was driving to meet my friends mostly because I didnt know what to expect…and also bc I knew I would be without a bathroom close by for 2-3 hours (those with IBS will understand this!!)…
〰️
But with a little cognitive restructuring, positive self-talk, healing coping statements, peppermint oil, breathwork, and preparation… I had one of the best days I’ve had in years!
〰️
Maybe that sounds like a lot of prep, but now that I know what I need in my anxiety healing toolkit, I can more easily face my fears and stay away from avoidance! 
〰️
Thank you @bcrivercountry !!!It was honestly so incredibly fun and I felt so proud of myself for doing something outside of my comfort zone and kicking anxiety’s a** ☺️☺️👍👍
〰️
What have you done lately to kick anxiety’s a** ?? Let me know in the comments!
〰️
Follow 👉 @theanxietyhealer for all things anxiety healing!
〰️

node.text:
Did you know there’s a difference between rational fear and anxiety (irrational fears)?
〰️
Fear and anxiety are both meant to protect us, but there are times when anxiety takes over and we may not know why...
〰️
And then we become fearful of our anxiety am I right?
〰️
If you or anyone you know is struggling with anxiety, just know that there is help out there and you WILL be ok...I know it may not feel like that in the moment, but there are amazing counselors who specialize in anxiety disorders ready to help!
〰️
I specialize in Cognitive Behavioral Therapy and it has been the most healing for my own anxiety and my clients, but there are many modalities out there...
〰️
Be your own advocate and know that you’re not alone...❤️❤️❤️ 
〰️
Follow 👉 @theanxietyhealer for all things anxiety healing!
〰️
